	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=25447&mid=107958372196254>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=25447&mid=107958372196254>MONKS BEWARE</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=25447&mid=107958372196254#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Mar 17th 11:23 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=184351><span id=Scholar>Glasshoppa the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>46 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.04]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Caution fellow monks! Using this discipline while feigned will break the feign. You can however use this disc and then FD and you'll be ok.<br><br>While there is rarely a good time to have your feign broken, where I learned the above was about the worst place it could happen. I was in Fear solo to do my turn in to Lord Cazic himself for the Whistling Fists. My guild had been there on a raid earlier that day and cleared most of the zone (cept CT) but I did not have all of the turn in pieces with me. Got to the ring of fire, hailed CT (who happens to love ikky monks) but I got proximity agro from a local mob so CT joined in. I successfully feigned but was down to about 20% so used this discipline to heal up a little while I waited for said baddies to wander off. Soon as I hit the Disc I see the message that I was no longer feigned...Loading Please Wait. &lt;sigh&gt; <br><br>Got my Whistling Fists from CT on second try after CR and gated out (thanks Thurg gate potion!) <br><br>Learn from the fallen monks before you. :-)</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Glasshoppa 65 Iksar Monk<br>Candylips 56 Troll Beast<br>Gnomicon 43 Gnome Necro<br>The Rathe</td></tr>
